cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it analyzes the topology of the Internet. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies the distribution of curvatures in the network and its connections to various measures. Additionally, it could be categorized as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it uses mathematical tools to analyze the network topology. It could also be classified as cs.IT (Information Theory) as it studies the reliability of routes in the network. Finally, it could be categorized as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as it analyzes the geometric structures in complex network theory.
